{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-post-template-tsx","path":"/posts/using-oh-my-zsh-to-optimize-the-shell/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"9e2620f6-43b0-51d5-bfce-ca8a18a10267","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9a7eee38d767131a6e05cbcf878106f5/4b190/oh-my-zsh-logo.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 40%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/9a7eee38d767131a6e05cbcf878106f5/8ac56/oh-my-zsh-logo.webp 240w,\n/static/9a7eee38d767131a6e05cbcf878106f5/d3be9/oh-my-zsh-logo.webp 480w,\n/static/9a7eee38d767131a6e05cbcf878106f5/d00b9/oh-my-zsh-logo.webp 800w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/9a7eee38d767131a6e05cbcf878106f5/09b79/oh-my-zsh-logo.jpg 240w,\n/static/9a7eee38d767131a6e05cbcf878106f5/7cc5e/oh-my-zsh-logo.jpg 480w,\n/static/9a7eee38d767131a6e05cbcf878106f5/4b190/oh-my-zsh-logo.jpg 800w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/9a7eee38d767131a6e05cbcf878106f5/4b190/oh-my-zsh-logo.jpg\"\n            alt=\"oh-my-zsh\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"why-do-we-need-to-optimize-the-shell\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#why-do-we-need-to-optimize-the-shell\" aria-label=\"why do we need to optimize the shell permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Why do we need to optimize the shell?</h2>\n<p>The shell is a key component of the Linux operating system. It provides a basic <strong>command line interface (CLI)</strong> to interact with the system kernel. As the principle of the Linux system design, the <strong>graphical user interface (GUI)</strong> is not always available for all users. The shell is the guaranteed way to ensure the kernel can be controlled by the user. Especially, some work is not suitable for GUI, such as system maintenance, server management, and so on.</p>\n<p>For the end-users, the shell is used to run commands, scripts, and programs. And for most of modern Linux systems, the <strong>Bourne Again SHell (bash)</strong> is the default one. But we can replace the default shell with another one, such as <strong>Z SHell (zsh)</strong>. The zsh is more powerful, user-friendly, customizable, modern, popular, feature-rich, interactive, efficient, secure, and fun than bash. So, it is a good choice to optimize the shell with zsh. The major improvement of zsh over bash is that it provides a more powerful scripting language, more advanced tab completion, and more customization options. It also has a more modern and user-friendly interface. By using the zsh, you can improve your productivity and make your shell more efficient and enjoyable to use.</p>\n<h2 id=\"oh-my-zsh\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#oh-my-zsh\" aria-label=\"oh my zsh permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>oh-my-zsh</h2>\n<p>As introduced by my friend, I learned there is a powerful zsh configuration framework called <strong>oh-my-zsh</strong>. It makes it easy to customize and enhance zsh with plugins, themes, and other features. By using oh-my-zsh, you can easily customize your zsh configuration and make it more powerful and user-friendly. You can also easily add new features and functionality to your shell by using the plugins provided by oh-my-zsh. You can also easily change the appearance of your shell by using the themes provided by oh-my-zsh. By using oh-my-zsh, you can make your shell more modern, feature-rich, interactive, efficient, secure, and fun.</p>\n<p>The installation of <strong>oh-my-zsh</strong> is very easy. Please just run the following command in your shell:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token function\">sh</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-c</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token function\">curl</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-fsSL</span> https://raw.githubusercontent.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh/master/tools/install.sh<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>\"</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>After that, don’t forget to change your default shell to the <strong>zsh</strong> by running the following command:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">chsh <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-s</span> <span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token function\">which</span> <span class=\"token function\">zsh</span><span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Then, you can restart your shell to see the changes.</p>\n<h2 id=\"conclusion\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#conclusion\" aria-label=\"conclusion permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>I’ve just started my journey with the <strong>zsh</strong> and <strong>oh-my-zsh</strong>. I found it to be very powerful and user-friendly. I hope more ane more people will join the community with me and enjoy the fun of the shell.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/2017-03-19---Using-\"oh my zsh\"-to-Optimize-the-Shell//posts/using-oh-my-zsh-to-optimize-the-shell","tagSlugs":["/tag/linux-system/","/tag/shell/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2017-03-19T15:30:00.000Z","description":"to improve your shell, please join the zsh community and use oh my zsh.","tags":["Linux System","Shell"],"title":"Using \"oh my zsh\" to Optimize the Shell","socialImage":{"publicURL":"/static/9a7eee38d767131a6e05cbcf878106f5/oh-my-zsh-logo.jpg"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/2017-03-19---Using-\"oh my zsh\"-to-Optimize-the-Shell//posts/using-oh-my-zsh-to-optimize-the-shell"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","288581551","401334301"],"slicesMap":{}}